<TITLE> HSBC CEO faces arrest in copyright case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Wednesday ordered arrest of the CEO of HSBC Bangladesh and two other senior officials in a copyright violation case. Two others accused were corporate banking division head Mohammad Mahbubur Rahman and head of finance Mostofa Alim Awlad. ANM Bashir Ullah, judge of Dhaka metropolitan sessions judges' court gave the order upon a case filed by renowned lyricist and singer Apel Mahmud on Oct 5. Mahmud alleged in his case that CEO Sanjay Prakash and other two were responsible selling a CD with his songs without his permission. The songs were such as 'Mora ekti phulke banchabo bole juddho kori (Just to save one flower we fight a war)' and 'Tir Hara Ei Dheuer Sagor Pari Debore (This endless rough sea we will cross)'. The CD with the title `Sotoborsher Bangla Gaan (A Century of Bangla Song)', had songs also performed by other artistes which is a crime as per copyright act, he also alleged. Abdul Mannan Khan, lawyer for Apel Mahmud, told bdnews24.com that the court ordered police to submit the warrant execution report on Nov 22. bdnew
